AB  - Trout stocking in the mid-1960s eliminated the calanoid copepod Hesperodiaptomus arcticus and other largebodied crustaceans such as Gammarus lacustris, Daphnia middendorfﬁana, and Daphnia pulex from many alpine lakes in the Rocky Mountain Parks of Canada. H. arcticus frequently dominates the plankton communities of ﬁshless lakes, preying on rotifers and nauplius larvae. Following the extirpation of H. arcticus, rotifers and small-bodied cyclopoid copepods dominate the zooplankton assemblages of alpine lakes.
