TI  - ECOLOGICAL RESTORATION OF LAGG-SWAMP SPECIES ON CUTOVER PEATLANDS
AB  - A relatively more recent challenge in restoration of cutover peatlands is the restoration of the lagg-swamp. That is, the minerotrophic band surrounding the dome in natural raised bogs. In our study, we follow three objectives: 1) to characterize the effects of shade on the regeneration of two typical moss species of natural lagg-swamps when reintroduced in cutover peatlands; 2) to characterize the effects of shade and presence of a moss carpet on the germination of one sedge species and one shrub species; 3) to characterize the effects of shade, presence of a moss carpet and fertilization on the growth and survival of shrub seedlings.
